   <titles>
      <title>Scalar Multiplication of Vectors - Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>When we multiply a vector <math>
                     <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                  </math> by a number (a scalar) <math>
                     <latex>t</latex>
                  </math>, we keep the direction of <math>
                     <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                  </math> and multiply its length by <math>
                     <latex>t</latex>
                  </math>. If <math>
                     <latex>t</latex>
                  </math> is positive, this has the effect illustrated below.</para.body>
            </para>
            <para align="center">
               <para.body>
                  <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                     <img src="ims/VectorScalarMultiply_2.gif"/>
                  </media>
               </para.body>
            </para>
            <para>
               <para.body>If we multiply a vector <math>
                     <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                  </math> by a negative number <math>
                     <latex>t</latex>
                  </math>, we reverse the direction of <math>
                     <latex>\mathbf{x}</latex>
                  </math>, as is illustrated in the picture below.</para.body>
            </para>
            <para align="center">
               <para.body>
                  <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                     <img src="ims/VectorScalarMultiply_3.gif"/>
                  </media>
               </para.body>
            </para>
            <para>
               <para.body>Here are a number of scalar multiplications performed on one and the same vector. Click <subordinate>
                     <hot>here</hot>
                     <info>
                        <info.caption>Animation of Scalar Multiplication of a Vector by a Number</info.caption>
                        <para align="center">
                           <para.body>
                              <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                                 <img src="ims/VectorScalarMultiply_Anmt.gif"/>
                              </media>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </info>
                  </subordinate> to animate this example.
		</para.body>
            </para>
            <para align="center">
               <para.body>
                  <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                     <img src="VectorScalarMultiply_1.gif"/>
                  </media>
               </para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
